-- Estonian c.bank cuts 2014 GDP growth forecast
-- By David Mardiste
-- Wed Dec 10, 2014 04:00AM EST
-- None



TALLINN, Dec 10 (Reuters) - Euro zone member Estonia's economy will grow slower than previously forecast in 2014 hurt by weakness in Europe, the central bank said in a statement on Wednesday.

The central bank lowered its forecast for growth in 2014 to 1.9 percent from the 2.1 percent seen in September and cut its forecast for next year to 2.1 percent from a previous estimate of 2.5 percent growth. [ID:L6N0RO2V4]  It also cut its forecast for growth in 2016 to 3.1 percent from its previous estimate of 3.6 percent. In the third quarter, Estonia's economy grew 2.2 percent compared to the same period a year ago, according to revised data from the statistics office.